
[1]felonious

   FELO'NIOUS, a.

   1. Malignant; malicious; indicating or proceeding from a depraved heart
   or evil purpose; villainous; traitorous; perfidious; as a felonious
   deed.

   2. In law, proceeding from an evil heart or purpose; done with the
   deliberate purpose to commit a crime; as felonious homicide.
